From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Date: Wed, 16 Mar 2011 14:45:31 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 028/307] arm: Mark pmu interupt IRQF_NO_THREAD
Origin: https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/rt/linux-stable-rt.git/commit?id=2f44af45e7d6ee3b92de4f7ba8c2ce664ffdeb36

PMU interrupt must not be threaded. Remove IRQF_DISABLED while at it
as we run all handlers with interrupts disabled anyway.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
---
 arch/arm/kernel/perf_event.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/kernel/perf_event.c b/arch/arm/kernel/perf_event.c
index a559ee7..3ecce1b 100644
--- a/arch/arm/kernel/perf_event.c
+++ b/arch/arm/kernel/perf_event.c
@@ -438,7 +438,7 @@ armpmu_reserve_hardware(struct arm_pmu *armpmu)
 		}
 
 		err = request_irq(irq, handle_irq,
-				  IRQF_DISABLED | IRQF_NOBALANCING,
+				  IRQF_NOBALANCING | IRQF_NO_THREAD,
 				  "arm-pmu", armpmu);
 		if (err) {
 			pr_err("unable to request IRQ%d for ARM PMU counters\n",
